                  <handDesc>
                     <!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script">Fine and careful</ab>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" corresp="PRS00000">Gäbrä Waḥǝd</persName>Gäbrä Waḥǝd
                        is mentioned as the scribe in the concluding supplication (fol. 47rb
                        l.5).&#xD; He appears to be the same scribe as that of DZ-019.<date>late
                           19th century</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The handwriting is fine and regular;
                        the letters are right-sloping, slender, with a few distinctive
                        features:<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> - body of ደ and የ is often shaped as
                        triangle<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> - vowel markers are notably long in
                        such letters as e.g. ሕ, ቡ, ቢ, ቲ,
                        ኒ<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic"> - short "hairlines" extending
                        horizontal elements of some letters (e.g. መ, በ, ወ, የ,
                        ደ)<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic"> - the right loop of ማ, ሚ, ሠ and ሢ is
                        of smaller
                        size<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic"> - the words እግዚአብሔር፡ and እግዚእ፡ are
                        usually written with
                        ligature.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h8" script="Ethiopic"> The handwriting is very similar to
                        that of
                        DZ-019.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">Fol. 2r (incipit page of Text I-1):
                        elaborate coloured (red, orange-brown, green, black) ornamental band with
                        one central and two lateral pendants reaching the bottom of the page;
                        interlaces, geometric, and anthropomorphic motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2"/>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d3">Coloured ornamental bands with different
                        motifs are drawn throughout the text at the beginning of each section; fols.
                        6rb (interlaces), 9va (geometric motifs), 15ra (interlaces), 19ra (geometric
                        motifs), 27ra (geometric motifs), 31ra (floral motifs), 33ra (geometric
                        motifs), 37rb (interlaces), 40rb (geometric motifs), 42rb (geometric
                        motifs), 44rb (geometric motifs).</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#47va">Fol. 47va</locus>-b: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 47va: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘአጽሐፈ፡ በወርቁ፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡ ወስመ፡ አቡሁ፡
                              ሰይፈ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ሕይወት፡ ወብዕሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ጻድቃን፡ ወደቂቁ፡ ተክለ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወለተ፡
                              ዮሐንስ፡ ወእሁኁ፡ ወልደ፡ ሱራፌል። ዘወሀቦ፡ ለመቅደሰ፡ ቂርቆስ። ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/> The not states that Gäbrä Ḥǝywät is the commissioner
                           and donor of this Ms. His family members are also mentioned: his wife
                           Wälättä Ṣadǝqan, his father Säyfä Mikaʾel, his mother Wälättä Ḥǝywät, his
                           children Täklä Mikaʾel and Wälättä Yoḥannǝs, his brother Wäldä Surafel. </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#47vb">Fol. 47vb</locus>: Short purchase note. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/> The note is written beneath Additio 1 in a different
                           hand. Gäbrä Ḥǝywät's relatives are mentioned. </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the work is written on the back board.&#xD;
                           - Crude drawings and scribbles: fols. 1rv, 48v, 49r.&#xD; - Writing
                           exercise: fol. 49v.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
